## Core Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `skills-seed init` | Initialize a project or workspace root. |
| `skills-seed reset` | Back up `.skills-seed` and recreate local skills-seed state. |
| `skills-seed workspace add` | Add detected child repositories to a workspace. |
| `skills-seed sync` | Learn current changes and regenerate Skills when needed. |
| `skills-seed learn current` | Learn from current files without separately running generation. |
| `skills-seed learn history` | Learn from recent Git commits. |
| `skills-seed generate skills` | Render Skills from existing learned state. |
| `skills-seed patterns add` | Create a durable pattern from explicit guidance. |
| `skills-seed patterns update` | Update a durable pattern. |
| `skills-seed patterns delete` | Delete a pattern; aliases: `rm`, `remove`. |
| `skills-seed patterns show` | List patterns or show one pattern. |
| `skills-seed patterns stats` | Show pattern quality and check hit statistics. |
| `skills-seed patterns compact` | Deduplicate or merge patterns. |
| `skills-seed workflow` | Create or update task workflows. |
| `skills-seed workflow show` | List workflow summaries or inspect one workflow. |
| `skills-seed preview files` | Inspect analysis file selection. |
| `skills-seed check` | Review staged or tracked files. |
| `skills-seed review import` | Import review feedback from JSON. |
| `skills-seed review stats` | Measure pattern coverage against imported review feedback. |
| `skills-seed profile show` | Inspect the project profile. |
| `skills-seed profile refresh` | Refresh the project profile with AI. |
| `skills-seed hook install` | Install the pre-commit integration. |
| `skills-seed hook run` | Run the pre-commit workflow manually. |
| `skills-seed hook uninstall` | Remove the pre-commit integration. |
| `skills-seed log` | Show recent skills-seed learning/generation changes. |
| `skills-seed help [command]` | Show root or nested command help. |
| `skills-seed --version` | Show CLI and template fingerprints. |
| `skills-seed cli-skills install` | Install or update this global CLI operation Skill. |
| `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall` | Remove this generated global CLI operation Skill. |

## Default Workflows

1. First project setup: `skills-seed init`, then `skills-seed sync`.
2. First workspace setup: `skills-seed init --workspace`, then `skills-seed workspace add .`, then `skills-seed sync`.
3. Daily update: `skills-seed sync`.
4. Add a durable rule: `skills-seed patterns add --context "<rule>"`, then `skills-seed generate skills`.
5. Add a durable task process: `skills-seed workflow --name <name> --context "<process>"`, then `skills-seed generate skills`.
6. Debug file selection: `skills-seed preview files --mode current` before learning.
7. Pre-commit review: `skills-seed check` or install the hook with `skills-seed hook install`.
